text: ShakeAlert uses a network of seismometers to detect earthquakes seconds before they occur, identifying the seismic waves that cause major ground shaking and sending alerts so that people know about the quake seconds or even a minute before shaking begins. https://t.co/sPgt0nmvrs

name: sfchronicle
text:
Fine dining domes are "a perfect symbol of the complete inadequacy of our social safety net," writes critic Soleil Ho. Diners can pay to eat inside the structures in Mint Plaza, an area where many people, both unhoused and housed, often congregate.
https://t.co/74QA6ML9iy
